China is set to complete its first blood bank for pandas, aiding in research on their blood types and transfusion compatibility.
With only 1,600 pandas in the wild, conservation efforts are crucial, especially for the Qinling subspecies.
Threats like poaching and habitat loss persist, impacting the survival of these iconic bears.
In response, China has established nature reserves and increased forest coverage to protect the pandas' habitats.
Recent reports of pandas facing starvation due to bamboo blooming highlight the ongoing challenges in preserving this endangered species.
Efforts are underway to relocate and care for affected pandas to ensure their survival.
